Niles Welch https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niles_Welch 0 Niles Eugene Welch (July 29, 1888 – November 21, 1976) was an American performer on Broadway, and a leading man in a number of silent and early talking motion pictures from the early 1910s through the 1930s.
